text: Ágnes Bánfai (8 June 1947 - 20 August 2020) was a Hungarian gymnast. She competed at the 1968 Summer Olympics in all gymnastics events. She finished in fifth place in the team competition. She won a bronze medal with the Hungarian team at the 1974 World Artistic Gymnastics Championships.Ágnes Bánfai. sports- reference.com She was born in Budapest.
